dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.proto.bridge.BridgingProtocol
dataStructure.description:
Bridging Protocols operate at the data link layer of the OSI model, and are used to define communications over different types of homogeneous and heterogeneous local area networks. The DEN-ng model defines RSRBridging, SRBridging, SRTBridging, and TransparentBridging as examples of subclasses of this class.

This entity is abstract

This entity is optional
